                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/145.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Vice
                        Consul <persName type="to">Davis</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 9, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your March 8. Department telegraphing Carothers as suggested. Has telegram from
                    him dated March 7, stating: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Have held up payment of tax in Guadalajara until some agreement is
                            reached. Authorities claim it is State tax and not forced loan. Will
                            report results later.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
